This paper deals with neural networks and their application to sparse coding and image inpainting, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) communities. The paper also discusses the use of iterative solvers and their convergence rates, which are topics that fall under the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) categories. Finally, the paper introduces an adaptive learning scheme, which is a topic that is relevant to the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI).
